caption: Shhhhh, be vewy vewy quiet! I’m making wabbits! 🐰 😁🐰Sweetest little egg cosy pattern by @littlecottonrabbits 🐰🐰🐰

Gloomy and cool weather here today makes think about my first knitted Fairisle beanie and fingerless mittens for a #throwbackthursday #tbt These colours bring me sheer joy and fit in perfectly with the Easter colours I’ve been using lately.

Adding to my egg collection this afternoon in the gorgeous colours of @kpcyarn Glencoul! 🥚 🐣 🥚 I had almost forgotten about Easter coming up with everything that has been happening. So looking forward to a few days of crochet and knitting 🧶
If you are self isolating somewhere and cannot get outdoors, I hope this brings a smile to your face 🙂🙂🙂An old blanket of mine but definitely a goodie 💖💖💖#allthecolours #crochetinthegreatoutdoors
Hhhmmmm, bubble gum colours! 💖🐣💖😁Another knitted egg to add to my collection in @kpcyarn Glencoul 💖💖💖Ill have to get some crocheted ones done too

It’s been a good, slow Sunday working on another knitted Easter egg.  I don’t often use a lot of mauve but with a little inspiration from some lavender, I love it 💖Some of you asked me for patterns on my previous post. There are plenty of knitted egg patterns out there and different ways they can be made. Check out @purlsoho , @arnecarlos and @littlecottonrabbits 🐰 The little bunny egg cosy is based on a pattern on a blog called Marianna’s Lazy Daisy Days 🐰 All knitted in my favourite @kpcyarn Glencoul colours. Hope you had a lazy Sunday too. Take care out there everybody! 💖💖💖
Surely it’s not too early for a bit of Easter magic? Well, you know it’s never too early for Easter chocolate!!! And stop calling me Shirley! 😂😂😂 #crochetgirl99knits2
A bowl of colourful goodness for your Friday! 💖💚💛💙I do believe the world is going crazy at the moment. Keep calm and look at some yarn! 🧶

I may be late but I did eventually finish my knit/crochet “welcome to March” project 💖💚💖That’s 3 done for the year and only 9 more to go 😲 I’m working on a wall calendar that will eventually have crocheted numbers as well. It works in theory but sometimes reality can be different 😂😂😂

Just a little bit more green and blue for my gallery 💚💙💚I’m loving this Paris in Berlin Cowl by @jojilocat in @wrenandollie 4ply sock yarn in the Willow colour. It’s such a gorgeous colour. I had put it away to make some socks but then I discovered this pattern 💚💙💚Have an awesome weekend!
Kits in the Spring/Summer colours of my Six Petal Flower Scarf are available again through @yummyyarnandco 🍃 🌊 🍃 I still adore these colours in the @vinniscolours Nikkim Cotton 💚💙💚
